title: Internal Compiler Error

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: E-needs-mcve
labels.description: Call for participation: This issue needs a Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example

body:
Today I encountered a compiler panic with rustc 1.64.0. ### Code Unfortunately I cannot provide the code at this point, as it's not released, yet. The project makes heavy use of (const) generics. There were some errors in the code which probably lead to the compiler panic. After fixing some errors, the panic went away, too. ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.64.0 binary: rustc commit-hash: unknown commit-date: unknown host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.64.0 LLVM version: 14.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/query/normalize.rs:257:21: unexpected ambiguity: Canonical {
